messages.content: So to give a basic rundown I'm going to attempt to make my own custom bass, but with some stuff already done because I don't wanna screw much up

roles.name: ssuper specil Mod role ow o

messages.content: I would be buying a bass like this (mainly shape wise, this one runs for $330 used)

roles.name: ssuper specil Mod role ow o

messages.content: And I'm gonna repaint it to look like this sorta vintage burst that I'm gonna do by hand

roles.name: ssuper specil Mod role ow o

messages.content: The biggest challenge I'm going to face is the pickups, as I would have to re route the cavities, and due to the fact that I want to have a clean finish, I would remove the top and rebuild one to look more sleek with the different pickup layouts

roles.name: ssuper specil Mod role ow o

messages.content: For the neck pickup I would be having a "Mudbucker" which is this huge neck pickup (Gibson eb0 bass for reference on size)

roles.name: ssuper specil Mod role ow o

messages.content: Now this is still up for the air but since I rarely use the bridge pickup on any of my basses, I would be adding a P bass style pickup in the middle (fender p bass for ref and where I would likely put it)

roles.name: ssuper specil Mod role ow o

messages.content: As for wiring I would be redoing the typical hofner style (two volumes, bass switch, treble switch and rthym switch, {which basically acts as another volume}) I would be custom doing it to fit a more broader sound since hollow basses do get very boomy, which I like but may not be for every song, (1 volume, 1 tone, bass switch, treble switch, strangle switch {makes it less bassy, highpass filter})

roles.name: ssuper specil Mod role ow o

messages.content: And currently this is in planning phase as I'm selling alot of things I don't use for cash for this (and for a new workshop)

roles.name: ssuper specil Mod role ow o

messages.content: I will post project updates on how it's going and when I do finish this, I will upload a video on the overall tone
